<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-688-828  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 688 828.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>InfoWorld  Sept 25 1989 v11 n39 p46(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Metamorphosis of the leaves heralds return of the worm. (Techstreet)(computer security) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Gantz, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Computer viruses are a growing concern with the introduction ofIBM's Repository database tool.andP;  Its giant data dictionary acts asa central clearinghouse for numerous distributed-processingnetworks and could increase the network dependence of business tothe point where a virus attack would cripple numerous companies.andO;An absolute virus-protection program would be self-defeatingbecause many useful programs, such as communications managementapplications, rely on subroutines similar to virus 'worms.' Theseprograms would cease to function under a virus-protection system.andO;Users are learning to live with the virus phenomenon, and'vaccine' programs have become a lucrative industry.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer VirusesComputer CrimesData SecurityData Bases.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>